POLICE SEEK OWNER OF TRUCK HIT BY TRAIN 
Authorities are searching for the owner of an empty pickup truck that was 
destroyed by a southbound Southern Pacific train in Newhall. 
There were no injuries and only minor damage to the train and tracks, said Lt. 
Marvin Dixon of the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department. The accident 
occurred between 10:30 p.m. and 11 p.m. Sunday. 
Dixon said deputies were investigating how the truck got on the tracks, near 
Market Street and parallel to Railroad Avenue in downtown Newhall. 
